'''Avatar Marketplace''' (AVM) is a feature of VRChat’s [[Creator Economy]], providing a platform for creators to sell monetized [[avatars]] directly within VRChat using [[Creator Economy#VRChat_Credits|VRC Credits]].

==Overview==
The Avatar Marketplace allows for users to buy and use avatars from creators natively within VRChat, streamlining the process compared to third-party platforms. Purchased avatars can be immediately used without uploading them via Unity or the [[VRChat SDK]].

Selecting the '''Avatars''' Quick Link in the [[Quick Menu]] opens the Avatar tab in the [[Main Menu]], defaulting to the '''Explore''' section. This section features both free [[Public Avatars|public avatars]] and paid avatars available via the Marketplace.
